{"id": "2026-07-24-news-us-hits-switzerland-with-12-5-tariff-over-forced", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "US hits Switzerland with 12.5% tariff over forced-labour claims", "summary": "Washington imposed a 12.5% tariff on Swiss goods from 24 July as its temporary 10% levy expired, the top rate in a Section 301 forced-labour action against 60 economies.", "url": "https://ustr.gov/about/policy-offices/press-office/press-releases/2026/july/ustr-takes-action-forced-labor-section-301-investigations", "source_domain": "ustr.gov", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["official PR"], "topics": ["switzerland", "economy"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "The US slapped a new 12.5% tariff on Swiss goods from 06:01 Swiss time on Friday 24 July, the top rate in a forced-labour trade action hitting 60 economies. The US Trade Representative, Jamieson Greer, took \"final action\" under Section 301 of the 1974 Trade Act — the same durable legal tool Trump used against China in his first term — imposing 10% on partners that pledged to enforce a ban on imports made with forced labour and 12.5% on those USTR judged to have \"failed to adopt\" such a ban; Switzerland drew the higher rate. The levies took effect at 12:01am Washington time (04:01 GMT), the moment the temporary 10% worldwide tariff — a 150-day Section 122 stopgap adopted after the Supreme Court struck down Trump's broader IEEPA tariffs in February — expired. Swiss business reaction was immediate and hostile, with employers' groups quoted calling the move \"unjustified and incomprehensible,\" and SRF noting Switzerland comes off worse than the EU, whose separate July trade deal caps most goods at a 15% all-inclusive ceiling.", "why": "It lands a fresh, above-EU cost on Swiss exporters — pharma, machinery, watches — just as the prior tariff truce lapses, and reframes a US trade dispute as a human-rights enforcement claim against Swiss supply chains that Bern rejects.", "thread_id": "2026-07-24-news-us-hits-switzerland-with-12-5-tariff-over-forced", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-24", "event_date": "2026-07-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Switzerland", "United States", "USTR"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-swiss-transport-regulator-orders-cash-and-paper", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "Swiss transport regulator orders cash and paper-ticket options preserved", "summary": "The Federal Office of Transport told operators on 24 July they must guarantee analogue, cash-payable ticket options as machines and cash acceptance disappear.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/analoge-alternativen-gefordert-bargeld-verschwindet-im-oev-jetzt-greift-der-bund-ein", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Federal Office of Transport (BAV) told Switzerland's public-transport operators on Friday 24 July that they must guarantee analogue, cash-payable ticket options as machines and cash acceptance disappear. In a written directive to the industry, the BAV said every transport company must ensure that people who cannot or do not want to buy tickets digitally still have a way to obtain a valid one; spokesperson Andreas Windlinger said such passengers \"should not be left behind.\" The rules are binding. The industry body Alliance SwissPass defended its digitalisation drive but said it would comply, pointing to existing options such as loading a ticket onto a SwissPass by phone in some regions.", "why": "It is a concrete federal check on the cashless push in daily Swiss life, protecting older passengers and those without smartphones from being locked out of the transport network.", "thread_id": "2026-07-24-news-swiss-transport-regulator-orders-cash-and-paper", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-24", "event_date": "2026-07-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["BAV", "Alliance SwissPass", "Switzerland"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-swiss-drought-grounds-steam-trains-amid-renewed", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "Swiss drought grounds steam trains amid renewed heatwave", "summary": "Several Swiss heritage railways parked their steam locomotives over wildfire risk as drought and a renewed heatwave gripped the country.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/waldbrandgefahr-in-der-schweiz-wegen-trockenheit-dampflokomotiven-bleiben-im-depot", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "A renewed heatwave and entrenched drought pushed several Swiss heritage railways to park their steam locomotives this week over wildfire risk. Operators pulled steam trains from service because glowing embers from the engines could ignite tinder-dry vegetation, SRF reported, as forecasters warned the heat would persist and the dryness would deepen.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-24-news-swiss-drought-grounds-steam-trains-amid-renewed", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-24", "event_date": "2026-07-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Switzerland"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-us-strikes-iran-for-13th-night-as-brent-crude-to", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "US strikes Iran for 13th night as Brent crude tops $100", "summary": "US forces bombed Iran for a 13th consecutive night into 24 July, Tehran rejected an Iraq-relayed ceasefire, and Brent crude closed above $100 for the first time since May.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/24/us-attacks-iran-as-houthis-allow-chinese-ships-to-pass-whats-the-latest", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "US forces bombed Iran for a 13th consecutive night into Friday 24 July, Tehran rejected a ceasefire relayed by Iraq's prime minister, and Brent crude closed above $100 a barrel for the first time since May. US Central Command said it concluded its latest round of strikes at 01:00 GMT Friday, hitting military command centres, drone-storage sites, communications networks and coastal surveillance; Iranian media reported explosions across Khondab, Khorramabad, Bandar Abbas and Qeshm island in the Strait of Hormuz, with Iran's Tasnim agency reporting four killed and five wounded near Ahvaz. Trump told Axios he might launch his largest strikes yet after Iran's retaliatory salvoes on Gulf US allies, which included hitting a telecoms tower in Kuwait, and Tehran warned it would hold accountable any country that supports a US strike. Shipping data showed just one tanker crossing Hormuz on Thursday — the lowest since 7 May — while Yemen's Houthis pressed a Red Sea blockade, though two Chinese supertankers carrying Saudi crude cleared the Bab al-Mandeb strait on Friday.", "why": "An open-ended US bombing campaign, a collapsed ceasefire track and oil back over $100 point to a widening Gulf war whose energy-price shock reaches well beyond the region.", "thread_id": "2026-06-20-cyber-papers-iran-closes-strait-of-hormuz-again-over-israeli", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-20", "event_date": "2026-07-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Iran", "United States", "Strait of Hormuz"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-spain-declares-national-emergency-as-wildfires-r", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "Spain declares national emergency as wildfires rage across southern Europe", "summary": "Spain declared its first fire-triggered national emergency late on 23 July as Madrid-area blazes forced 10,000 evacuations and a Gironde fire drove 40,000 from their homes in France.", "url": "https://www.france24.com/en/spain-declares-wildfire-emergency-10-000-evacuated-near-madrid", "source_domain": "france24.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Spain declared a national emergency over wildfires late on Thursday 23 July — its first ever triggered by fire — as blazes near Madrid and in Ávila forced about 10,000 evacuations, while France's Gironde fire drove some 40,000 people from their homes. Madrid invoked the emergency to speed the deployment of firefighting resources; France 24 called the Gironde blaze the largest of the season, still out of control, with tourists among those fleeing, and fires also burning in Italy amid a Europe-wide heatwave. The escalation follows Wednesday's deaths of three firefighters across France, Spain and Italy.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-23-news-wildfires-kill-three-firefighters-across-france", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-23", "event_date": "2026-07-23", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Spain", "France", "Gironde"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-four-palestinians-and-one-israeli-killed-in-west", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "Four Palestinians and one Israeli killed in West Bank shooting", "summary": "Israeli and Palestinian officials reported five dead in a shooting in the occupied West Bank on 24 July amid sharply rising settler-Palestinian violence.", "url": "https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20260724-four-palestinians-and-one-israeli-killed-in-occupied-west-bank-shooting", "source_domain": "france24.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Four Palestinians and one Israeli were killed in a shooting in the occupied West Bank on Friday 24 July, Israeli and Palestinian officials said. Both sides confirmed the deaths, though a full account of the incident was still emerging; France 24 noted violence between Israeli settlers and troops and Palestinians has risen sharply across the occupied territory since the start of the Gaza war.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-24-news-four-palestinians-and-one-israeli-killed-in-west", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-24", "event_date": "2026-07-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Israel", "Palestinians", "West Bank"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-ukraine-drone-strike-sets-fire-to-wildberries-wa", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "Ukraine drone strike sets fire to Wildberries warehouse near St Petersburg", "summary": "A Ukrainian drone attack set a Wildberries warehouse ablaze near St Petersburg early 24 July, wounding three, while a separate missile strike on Kirov killed six.", "url": "https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20260724-ukraine-drone-attack-sparks-fire-at-russian-e-commerce-giant-s-warehouse-near-saint-petersburg", "source_domain": "france24.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "A Ukrainian drone strike set a warehouse of Russian e-commerce giant Wildberries ablaze near St Petersburg early Friday 24 July, wounding at least three, while a separate Ukrainian missile strike on the city of Kirov killed six. Russian regional officials reported the casualties; Kyiv described the Kirov target as a military enterprise. The strikes extend Ukraine's deep-rear campaign against Russian logistics and industry hundreds of kilometres from the front.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-24-news-ukraine-drone-strike-sets-fire-to-wildberries-wa", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-24", "event_date": "2026-07-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Ukraine", "Russia", "Wildberries", "St Petersburg"]}
{"id": "2026-07-24-news-six-candidates-set-out-visions-to-succeed-guterr", "date": "2026-07-24", "stream": "news", "headline": "Six candidates set out visions to succeed Guterres as UN chief", "summary": "Six candidates for UN secretary-general presented their platforms on 23 July as the organisation faces a financial and confidence crisis ahead of a January 2027 leadership change.", "url": "https://www.france24.com/en/six-candidates-vying-to-become-the-next-un-secretary-after-guterres", "source_domain": "france24.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Six candidates to succeed Antonio Guterres as UN secretary-general set out their platforms on Thursday 23 July, with the world body facing a financial and confidence crisis. The contenders presented competing visions for reform ahead of a selection process that will decide the UN's leadership from January 2027; France 24 framed trust and credibility as the debate's dominant themes.", "why": "The next secretary-general inherits a cash-strapped, authority-challenged UN at a moment of active great-power conflict, making the choice more consequential than the usual succession.", "thread_id": "2026-07-24-news-six-candidates-set-out-visions-to-succeed-guterr", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-24", "event_date": "2026-07-23", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["United Nations", "Antonio Guterres"]}
